see you get there.

95
00:11:50,160 --> 00:11:51,957  X1:000 X2:719 Y1:002 Y2:574
(laughter)

96
00:11:52,080 --> 00:11:54,435  X1:000 X2:719 Y1:002 Y2:574
I'm terribly sorry!

97
00:11:56,240 --> 00:11:59,516  X1:000 X2:719 Y1:002 Y2:574
That's a custom. The bride
always gets to kiss her best man.

98
00:12:01,520 --> 00:12:04,239  X1:000 X2:719 Y1:002 Y2:574
- I thought it was the other way round.
- Oh.

99
00:12:05,480 --> 00:12:09,951  X1:000 X2:719 Y1:002 Y2:574
Oh, James, would you mind? Felix is still
in the study and we've got to cut the cake.

100
00:12:10,080 --> 00:12:14,073  X1:000 X2:719 Y1:002 Y2:574
- I'll do anything for a woman with a knife.
- Thank you. Could you help me?

101
00:12:24,560 --> 00:12:27,358  X1:000 X2:719 Y1:002 Y2:574
- Sorry.
- No, we're finished. Pam, meet James.

102
00:12:27,480 --> 00:12:29,072  X1:000 X2:719 Y1:002 Y2:574
Goodbye, Felix.

103
00:12:32,760 --> 00:12:35,957  X1:000 X2:719 Y1:002 Y2:574
- Strictly business, my friend.
- Switch that thing off, Felix.

104
00:12:36,080 --> 00:12:39,959  X1:000 X2:719 Y1:002 Y2:574
- You have a house full of guests waiting.
- Just let me save this. Take a seat.

105
00:12:40,080 --> 00:12:44,870  X1:000 X2:719 Y1:002 Y2:574
The department wants a full report...
yesterday. We really hit it lucky today.

106
00:12:45,200 --> 00:12:47,634  X1:000 X2:719 Y1:002 Y2:574
Sanchez hasn't been out
of his home base for years.

107
00:12:47,760 --> 00:12:51,196  X1:000 X2:719 Y1:002 Y2:574
- Couldn't you extradite him?
- He's killed, intimidated or bribed...

108
00:12:51,320 --> 00:12:53,595  X1:000 X2:719 Y1:002 Y2:574
..half the officials from here to Chile.

109
00:12:53,720 --> 00:12:56,553  X1:000 X2:719 Y1:002 Y2:574
There's only one law
down there - Sanchez's law.

110
00:12:56,920 --> 00:12:59,912  X1:000 X2:719 Y1:002 Y2:574
- Plomo o plata.
- Lead or silver.

111
00:13:00,040 --> 00:13:02,554  X1:000 X2:719 Y1:002 Y2:574
- Ah.
- Ed.

112
00:13:02,680 --> 00:13:05,114  X1:000 X2:719 Y1:002 Y2:574
Double congratulations, old buddy.

113
00:13:05,240 --> 00:13:08,516  X1:000 X2:719 Y1:002 Y2:574
You take your time on the honeymoon.
Everything's OK.

114
00:13:08,640 --> 00:13:11,837  X1:000 X2:719 Y1:002 Y2:574
You must be Bond.
The guy who came along for the ride.

115
00:13:12,200 --> 00:13:14,077  X1:000 X2:719 Y1:002 Y2:574
Ed Killifer.

116
00:13:14,200 --> 00:13:17,158  X1:000 X2:719 Y1:002 Y2:574
We're takin' Sanchez
to Quantico this afternoon.

117
00:13:17,280 --> 00:13:19,874  X1:000 X2:719 Y1:002 Y2:574
- Stay and have a drink with us.
- Gotta get back.

118
00:13:20,000 --> 00:13:22,434  X1:000 X2:719 Y1:002 Y2:574
I just came by to kiss the bride.

119
00:13:23,480 --> 00:13:28,349  X1:000 X2:719 Y1:002 Y2:574
- Felix, time to cut the cake.
- Oh. Hand me the picture of Della, quick.

120
00:13:32,280 --> 00:13:33,793  X1:000 X2:719 Y1:002 Y2:574
She must be ready to kill me.

121
00:13:40,760 --> 00:13:42,716  X1:000 X2:719 Y1:002 Y2:574
- I tied 'em myself.
- What are these?

122
00:13:42,840 --> 00:13:45,673  X1:000 X2:719 Y1:002 Y2:574
- Lures.
- These'll keep you busy for a few days.

123
00:13:45,800 --> 00:13:48,951  X1:000 X2:719 Y1:002 Y2:574
You're not going fishing
on my honeymoon.

124
00:13:51,040 --> 00:13:56,273  X1:000 X2:719 Y1:002 Y2:574
- How many others are being held there?
- Where are you taking him, Mr Killifer?

125
00:13:56,400 --> 00:13:59,836  X1:000 X2:719 Y1:002 Y2:574
Mr Sanchez, will you look
this way for a picture, please?

126
00:13:59,960 --> 00:14:03,157  X1:000 X2:719 Y1:002 Y2:574
- Come on! Get him inside!
- What is your real nationality?

127
00:14:03,280 --> 00:14:06,636  X1:000 X2:719 Y1:002 Y2:574
- Are you really Colombian?
- Have you been fairly treated?

128
00:14:06,760 --> 00:14:08,193  X1:000 X2:719 Y1:002 Y2:574
One more picture!

129
00:14:08,320 --> 00:14:11,551  X1:000 X2:719 Y1:002 Y2:574
Are you connected with
any laboratories in South America?

130
00:14:11,680 --> 00:14:15,832  X1:000 X2:719 Y1:002 Y2:574
- No more questions, now!
- Do you expect to be vindicated?

131
00:14:19,280 --> 00:14:21,635  X1:000 X2:719 Y1:002 Y2:574
OK, let's go.

132
00:14:31,840 --> 00:14:33,796  X1:000 X2:719 Y1:002 Y2:574
